<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><template xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns="openEHR/v1/Template" xmlns:uuid="java:java.util.UUID"><id>3aa8d997-3f91-4c96-bed4-9a8feb0468a4</id><name>RESP DIAG Cardiopulmonary Exercise Test %E2%80%93 Pediatric Order</name><description><lifecycle_state>Initial</lifecycle_state><details><purpose>For ordering a(n) Cardiopulmonary Exercise Test – Pediatric</purpose><use/><misuse/></details><other_details><item><key>MetaDataSet:Sample Set </key><value>Template metadata sample set </value></item><item><key>Acknowledgements</key><value/></item><item><key>Business Process Level</key><value/></item><item><key>Care setting</key><value/></item><item><key>Client group</key><value/></item><item><key>Clinical Record Element</key><value/></item><item><key>Copyright</key><value/></item><item><key>Issues</key><value/></item><item><key>Owner</key><value/></item><item><key>Sign off</key><value/></item><item><key>Speciality</key><value/></item><item><key>User roles</key><value/></item></other_details></description><annotations path="[openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1]"><items><item><key>Imaging.Terminology Mapping</key><value>4.47346005E8</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Clinical Decision Support Requirements</key><value>Physician: Please ensure the patient is well enough to do a 3 second (Under 10 years) 6 second (Greater than 10 years) repeatable vital capacity maneuvers.</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Contraindications</key><value>Severe airflow limitations (FEV1 less than 50% of predicted) (Absolute); Myocardial infarction (Within the last 3 months) (Absolute); Resting Electrocardiogram (ECG) changes suggesting an acute or recent myocardial event (Absolute); Unstable angina, cardiac ischemia or malignant arrhythmia (Absolute); Room air desaturation less than 85% (Absolute); Acute / uncontrolled asthma; Recent emboli's (Absolute); Unstable / uncontrolled diabetes (Absolute); Syncope (Absolute); Active endocarditis, myocarditis, or pericarditis (Absolute); Thrombosis of lower extremity (Absolute); Pulmonary edema (Absolute); Acute myocarditis or pericarditis (Absolute); Active endocarditis (Absolute); Acute non-cardiac disorder that may effect exercise performance or be aggravated by exercise (e.g. infection, renal failure) (Absolute); High-degree of atrioventricular block (Absolute); Inability to obtain consent (Absolute); Inability to perform acceptable and reproducible spirometry (Relative); Orthopedic or other limitations to exercise (Relative); Current or recent respiratory tract infection (Relative); Known electrolyte abnormalities (Relative); Uncontrolled hypertension, (Systolic blood pressure greater than 200 mmHg, diastolic blood pressure greater than 100 mmHg) (Relative); Left main coronary stenosis or its equivalent (Relative); Moderate stenotic valvular heart disease (Relative); Significant pulmonary hypertension (Relative); Advanced or complicated pregnancy (Relative); Abnormal ECG readings (Relative); Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy (Relative); Mental or physical impairment leading to inability to cooperate (Relative);</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Patient Requirements</key><value>Please refer to site specific patient information sheets for site guidelines on medication restrictions prior to test. </value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Ordering Clinician Instructions</key><value>May require a Pulmonologist to order or a Pulmonary consult. This is a specialized test, pre screening done based on site guidelines to determine appropriateness. Testing will only be performed on patients who are not on isolation, or isolation precautions cannot be provided for them.  Age restrictions as per site guidelines. </value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Clinical Communication</key><value>At Alberta Children's Hospital specific arrangements will be made for the Cystic Fibrosis clinic. </value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Recommended Use</key><value>Pediatric sites; Alberta Children's Hospital; University of Alberta Hospital </value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Synonyms</key><value>CPET; Exercise Tolerance Test; Cardiopulmonary Exercise Test</value></item><item><key>Technical.ﻩ Technical Traceabililty</key><value>{~AHSID~3aa8d997-3f91-4c96-bed4-9a8feb0468a4~NAME~RESP DIAG Cardiopulmonary Exercise Test %E2%80%93 Pediatric Order}</value></item></items></annotations><definition xsi:type="INSTRUCTION" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1" concept_name="Service request" max="1" name="Cardiopulmonary Exercise Test – Pediatric"/><integrity_checks xsi:type="ArchetypeIntegrity" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1"><digest id="MD5-CAM-1.0.1">AD8DFB192E67715F0D9E11E95E674AD0</digest></integrity_checks><integrity_checks xsi:type="ArchetypeIntegrity" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.service_request_information.v1"><digest id="MD5-CAM-1.0.1">230A8D964017E1FD7AC82EBDEE0202A6</digest></integrity_checks><integrity_checks xsi:type="ArchetypeIntegrity" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.adhoc_cluster_heading.v1"><digest id="MD5-CAM-1.0.1">B87630C57A2DB1AE21050E1105EDE18B</digest></integrity_checks></template>